<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="759" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">352.115/114: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Barcelona</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-10T21:00:00+00:00">October 10, 1936—9
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 11—1 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My October 8, 8 p.m. and October 9, 1 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">noon.</hi>] Galvet, delegate of Industry of Catalan Department
                                of Economy, gave assurances tonight that Catalan Government would
                                guarantee payment all cotton requisitioned and would get out formal
                                letter to that effect Monday after receiving up to date list all
                                American-owned cotton.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>